\f0\fs20 \cf0 [#Ellison2002;] actually finds female-authored papers experienced shorter submit-accept times than male-authored papers in the 1970s and 1980s, a sample which also included the *Review of Economics and Statistics*. I did not find this to be the case in my own sample when including similar controls---the coefficient remained positive albeit much smaller and insignificant (possibly due to the small number of female co-authors: only 14 papers published before 1990 were solo female-authored and only 48 had at least one female author).}

